RIYADH: Nahdi Medical Co., operator of one of the largest pharmacy chains in Saudi Arabia, saw its shares soar almost 23 percent three days into joining the stock exchange. Shares in the Jeddah-based firm extended gains by 1.4 percent to SR161 ($43) as of 10:39 a.m. Riyadh time on Thursday, compared to the initial public offering price of SR131. With the latest gain, the company now holds a record market valuation as high as SR20.9 billion. Ahead of listing, Nahdi had raised $1.36 billion in the biggest Saudi IPO since oil giant Aramco.